doc.previous: Unlike MatlinPatterson and Global Aero Logistics, Omni, which previously was with the Fedex team, has managed to steer clear of any conflict of interest issues since the economic upheaval of 2008, by competing solely upon one military bidding team. In 2012 Omni allied itself with the "New Patriot" Air Mobility Command (AMC) contracted airlift team[5] rather than risk the uncertainties of working with Federal Express as it had done in the past; and face difficulties similar to those that ATA Airlines found itself in, when its teaming contracts were unexpectedly cancelled by the aerial logistics giant.[6]
